observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Management:
Enjoin the Inventory Committee to: 
Perform the mandatory yearly physical count of properties to establish the existence and actual condition of the Property, Plant and Equipment owned by the Municipality;

properly prepare the RPCPPE and RPCRNS by supplying all the details needed therein;

Reconcile the results of the count with the property and accounting records; 

Submit the same to the Office of the Auditor within the set deadline; and

require the General Services Officer to maintain property cards and keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card and ensure that he performs his responsibility.

We reiterated our prior year’s recommendations that the LCE:
Require all concerned officers and employees to ensure that every Disbursement Voucher, Purchase Request, Purchase Order, Request for Quotations and Inspection and Acceptance Report is numbered sequentially, dated and that all necessary information in the documents is properly accomplished to give worthy credence as valid supporting documents;

Require all concerned officers and employees to ensure that the details in the supporting documents relating to claims of traveling expenses are always complete; 

All concerned officers and employees require the supplier to put their name or indicate their authority and sign the Purchase Order to bind them to the contract;

Require the drivers to ensure that the details in the Driver’s Trip Tickets are always complete; 

Ensure that a sound system of internal control is being installed, implemented and monitored in the Municipality in compliance with Section 124 of PD No. 1445.

We recommended that the Management:
Justify why they granted assistance for a private purpose;

Stop the transfer or grant of financial assistance for a private purpose;

Determine the projects, programs and activities in the Work Financial Plan (WFP) and budget that the NGO/PO may implement, and indicate in the WFP the purpose, specifications, intended beneficiaries and time frame. This will serve as the concrete basis for the granting of funds to the NGO/PO;

Evaluate properly the proposals of the NGOs/POs in accordance with the WFP and ensure that the required supporting documents are complete;

Obtain written concurrence from the Sangguniang Bayan for the transfer and grant of assistance to NGO/PO; and

strictly comply with all the provisions in the COA Circular No. 2007-001.

