We recommended that Management:

discontinues the practice of procuring goods and services on reimbursement basis, except for petty operating expenses, and emergency cases as provided by Section 53.2 of the Revised IRR of R.A. No. 9184 while complying with Section 4.1(b)(2) and (3) of COA Circular No. 85-55;

effect payment of goods and services through check payable to supplier or dealer except for petty operating expenses to be paid from petty cash fund and in case of emergency purchase;

procures goods and services in consonance with the approved Annual Procurement Plan and resort only to emergency purchases in cases of extreme danger to life and property; and

follows the proper procedures of procurement as provided under the Revised IRR of R.A. No. 9184 to obtain the most advantageous price to the government.

